  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Burkina - Agriculture - Promote local community resilience and national economic resilience</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There is an urgent need to protect and improve livelihoods in Burkina Faso. We must create opportunities by promoting resilience at community and national level, and by adapting our efforts to the fragile context. A key ambition is to protect and create jobs, with a special emphasis on women and youth.

Small and medium-sized economic operators in agriculture are experiencing inclusive growth in terms of turnover and job creation.

Build and strengthen community resilience within agrosylvopastoral households, including those of internally displaced persons (IDPs), in the target regions of the project.</narrative>
  </description>
